In this statement, the President condemns the attack on law enforcement in Baton Rouge. He expresses his support for the governor, mayor, sheriff's office, and police department, and assures that justice will be served. The motives behind the attack are unknown, but the President emphasizes that there is no justification for violence against law enforcement. He calls the attackers cowards who do not represent anyone or further any causes. The President asks for unity in prayer for the people of Baton Rouge, the wounded officers, and the families of the fallen.